Peugeot to Pay Back State Loan By April, Gales Tells Corriere

-- B y   T o m m a s o   E b h a r d t
-- 
2011-02-27T10:12:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-27/peugeot-to-pay-back-state-loan-by-april-gales-tells-corriere.html
PSA Peugeot Citroen plans to finish
paying back its loan from the French government by April, Jean-
Marc Gales, the head of the company’s Peugeot and Citroen
brands, told  Corriere della Sera  in an interview.  “We already paid back one billion euros ($1.38 billion),
we will reimburse the total debt by April,” Gales told the
Italian daily newspaper.  The French carmaker will also extend its partnership with  Bayerische Motoren Werke AG  to include a joint venture
developing hybrid-power components, which will be announced at
the Geneva International Motor Show, and plans to build a
factory in  India , Gales told the Italian daily.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tommaso Ebhardt in Milan at 
 tebhardt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  